.TH diameter 3 "diameter 2.6.1" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
diameter \- Main API of the diameter application.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This module provides the interface with which a user can implement a Diameter node that sends and receives messages using the Diameter protocol as defined in RFC 6733.

.PP
Basic usage consists of creating a representation of a locally implemented Diameter node and its capabilities with \fIstart_service/2\fR, adding transport capability using \fIadd_transport/2\fR and sending Diameter requests and receiving Diameter answers with \fIcall/4\fR. Incoming Diameter requests are communicated as callbacks to a \fIdiameter_app\fR callback modules as specified in the service configuration.

.PP
Beware the difference between \fIdiameter\fR (not capitalized) and \fIDiameter\fR (capitalized). The former refers to the Erlang application named diameter whose main api is defined here, the latter to Diameter protocol in the sense of RFC 6733.

.PP
The diameter application must be started before calling most functions in this module.

