eval() = {M,F,A} | fun() | [eval() | A]
.RS 2
An expression that can be evaluated as a function in the following sense.

.IP
.nf
eval([{M,F,A} | T]) ->
    apply(M, F, T ++ A);
eval([[F|A] | T]) ->
    eval([F | T ++ A]);
eval([F|A]) ->
    apply(F, A);
eval(F) ->
    eval([F]).

.fi

.PP
Applying an \fIeval()\fR \fIE\fR to an argument list \fIA\fR is meant in the sense of \fIeval([E|A])\fR.

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRBeware of using fun expressions of the form \fIfun Name/Arity\fR in situations in which the fun is not short-lived and code is to be upgraded at runtime since any processes retaining such a fun will have a reference to old code. In particular, such a value is typically inappropriate in configuration passed to \fIstart_service/2\fR or \fIadd_transport/2\fR.



