.fi

.PP
The RFC 3539 watchdog state machine has transitioned into (\fIup\fR) or out of (\fIdown\fR) the OKAY state. If a \fI#diameter_packet{}\fR is present in an \fIup\fR event then there has been a capabilities exchange on a newly established transport connection and the record contains the received CER or CEA.

.PP
Note that a single \fIup\fR or \fIdown\fR event for a given peer corresponds to multiple peer_up/3 or peer_down/3 callbacks, one for each of the Diameter applications negotiated during capabilities exchange. That is, the event communicates connectivity with the peer as a whole while the callbacks communicate connectivity with respect to individual Diameter applications.

.RE


